<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Sceliscelis marshi sp. nov., female paratype. Cephalothorax A dorsal and B ventral aspects C, D endogyne, ventral and dorsal aspects, respectively. Abbreviations: Bl - book lung operculum, ch - receptive chamber, ds - dorsal portion of scutum, Gr - grape-shaped glands, Ls - lateral sclerite, Re - rigid extension of posterior wall of epigastric fold, sco - scopula, Sr - sac like receptacle. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B), 0.2 mm (C, D)." , "Figure 1. Sceliscelis marshi sp. nov., male holotype A-C habitus in dorsal, ventral and lateral aspects D-F palp: D prolateral E ventral and F retrolateral aspects. Abbreviations: am-accompanying membrane, co - \" conductor, \" cy - cymbium, ds - dorsal portion of scutum, em - embolus, hle - hook-like extension, pe - palm-like embolic extension. Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C), 0.1 mm (D-F)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/436653" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/436652" .

